  "prompt": "How do you restore a Dell Inspiron B130 to the factory settings?",
  "response": "Restoring a Dell Inspiron B130 to factory settings involves reverting the laptop to its original out-of-the-box state. Here\u2019s how you can do it:\n\n---\n\n### **Method 1: Using the Built-in Recovery Partition**\nIf your Dell Inspiron B130 has a recovery partition, you can use it to restore the system to factory settings.\n\n1. **Backup Your Data**  \n   - Restoring to factory settings will erase all personal files, so back up any important data to an external drive or cloud storage.\n\n2. **Restart the Laptop**  \n   - Turn on your Dell Inspiron B130 or restart it if it\u2019s already on.\n\n3. **Access the Recovery Partition**  \n   - As the laptop boots, press the **F8** key repeatedly before the Windows logo appears. This will bring up the **Advanced Boot Options** menu.\n\n4. **Choose Repair Your Computer**  \n   - Use the arrow keys to select **Repair Your Computer** and press **Enter**.\n\n5. **Select Dell Factory Image Restore**  \n   - In the recovery options, choose **Dell Factory Image Restore** or **Restore System to Factory Defaults**.\n\n6. **Confirm the Restoration**  \n   - Follow the on-screen instructions to confirm the process. The laptop will restore itself to factory settings, which may take some time.\n\n7. **Complete the Setup**  \n   - After the process is complete, the laptop will restart and prompt you to set up Windows as if it were new.\n\n---\n\n### **Method 2: Using Recovery CDs/DVDs**\nIf you have recovery CDs or DVDs provided by Dell, you can use them to restore the system.\n\n1. **Insert the Recovery Disc**  \n   - Insert the first recovery CD/DVD into the optical drive.\n\n2. **Restart the Laptop**  \n   - Restart the laptop and press **F12** (or the designated boot menu key) during startup to access the boot menu.\n\n3. **Select the Optical Drive**  \n   - Choose the CD/DVD drive from the boot menu and press **Enter**.\n\n4. **Follow the On-Screen Instructions**  \n   - Follow the prompts to restore the laptop to factory settings. You may need to swap discs during the process.\n\n---\n\n### **Method 3: Using a Windows Installation Disc**\nIf you don\u2019t have a recovery partition or discs, you can use a Windows installation disc.\n\n1. **Insert the Windows Installation Disc**  \n   - Insert the disc into the optical drive.\n\n2. **Restart the Laptop**  \n   - Restart the laptop and press **F12** to access the boot menu.\n\n3. **Select the Optical Drive**  \n   - Choose the CD/DVD drive from the boot menu and press **Enter**.\n\n4. **Install Windows**  \n   - Follow the on-screen instructions to install Windows. During the installation, you\u2019ll be prompted to format the hard drive, which will erase all data.\n\n5. **Complete the Setup**  \n   - After installation, set up Windows as if it were a new system.\n\n---\n\n### **Important Notes**\n- If the recovery partition or discs are missing, you may need to contact Dell Support for assistance or download recovery media from Dell\u2019s official website if available.\n- Ensure the laptop is connected to a power source during the restoration process to avoid interruptions.\n- After restoring to factory settings, you\u2019ll need to reinstall any software or drivers that weren\u2019t included in the original setup.\n\nIf you encounter any issues, refer to Dell\u2019s official support documentation or contact Dell Support for further assistance.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
